title.narrative: VH2- QUALITY, INTEGRATED HIV SERVICES PROVISION (PREVENTION AND CARE)

description.narrative: By the end of 2021, health facilities and communities offer integrated, quality and equitable services for behavior change promotion, testing, Antiretroviral (ARV) treatment and monitoring of HIV viral load among children, adolescents and prevention of mother-to-child transmission, including in emergency situations., which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: More children, especially newborns, infants and young children reach their fifth birthday. Pregnant and lactating women, children and adolescents (girls and boys) infected and affected by HIV, particularly the most vulnerable, use holistic and integrated quality management and promotion for behavioral change to improve their survival. Fewer children under 5 suffer from stunting and acute malnutrition.

description.narrative: Les capacités de 63% des 405 structures de soins pratiquant la Prévention eTME ont été renforcées. 70% des 99 Unités de Prise en Charge offrent le traitement Antirétroviral pédiatrique. 26 laboratoires ont bénéficié de coaching des agents de santé (organisation et prestations de soins prénatals, accouchement, soins post-natals intégrant la PTME) et d’équipement en appareils et consommables pour le dépistage précoce et la mesure de la charge virale chez les enfants. L’Education Sexuelle Complète ciblant la prévention du VIH, des Infections Sexuellement Transmissibles et les grossesses précoces a été développée dans 10 arrondissements de Bangui, Bimbo et Begoua. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
